<br>
First lets list why this is happening. <br>
<br>
Well, Enchanters, Mages and Necro's can all solo fairly well with our new charms.  Enchanters can solo anywhere, where the Mages/Necro's have about one zone a piece... Bastion of Thunder for the mages, and Crypt of Decay for the necro's.  PoP was obviously developed with the high lvl, 6 man group or high dps raid.<br>
<br>
Frankely the way you're going about it now is, IMO, the wrong way.  This doesn't truely fix the situation with Charm.. it slows down the xp slightly, and doesn't really effect Necro's or Enchanters that much.  Enchanters don't Charm pets and keep them like mages do.  As Zeem pointed out in a different thread - Enchanters use a pet till it is almost dead, whether letting it go nearly toe to toe with another mob, or simply slowing the 'target' mobs until their pet is almost dead and then killing the pet. /charm /rinse /repeat<br>
<br>
Necro's - Well they agro kite at nearly zero risk... between root, fear and FD... they solo whether there's charm or not.<br>
<br>
Secondly it looks like you're attempting to keep Enchanters and Magicians from soloing the rune dropping rares in BoT.  Again these changes won't really effect this.  It certainly adds a little more risk, but doesn't keep 2 man groups from farming and holding a monopoly on these mobs.<br>
<br>
The issue at hand --<br>
Now that we know what we're trying to fix lets come up with some real fixes. <br>
<br>
The durations and the resists should be brought down. I agree with that.  But instead of 7.5min on the duration - maybe 10.5 to 15.5.  Why? Because frankely... time fly's in this game.  I don't want to feel like I have to recast the spell every two minutes.  The resists... with Tash and Malosinia you can keep it how it is OR keep the Enchanters at -50 and put mages to -10 or -20 just to give us a little help.<br>
<br>
Now you're all thinking WELL this doesn't change anything much at all! You're right... because the only way you can truely fix these charms is to take it out of the game OR...<br>
<br>
Put random spawns in the Tier 2 and 3 zones that mitigate slow or are unslowable.  The BoT mini bosses/rares should be unslowabe and more like the bosses in PoS that drop the medallions for the BoT quest. (IE requiring more then just a group)  Other randomly spawning mobs in the zone should have a chance to mitigate slow or be unslowable and possibly tagged uncharmable.  <br>
<br>
Again this may not really effect IF these classes can solo, but HOW they can solo... and what the risks are involved.  <br>
<br>
*So you're fighting a mob,.. you can't slow it.  No biggy? Well not until charm breaks and you have two unslowed mobs gunning for you.*<br>
<br>
...Then again Enchanters and Necro's have root, so maybe I'm just blowing smoke...  But as it stands now these 'fixes' to charm do nothing.<br>
<br>
And yes I know there's going to be those who say *Well I never wanted charm!*  Sorry folks but SoE isn't going to be taking it out of the game... for enchanters, necro's OR magicians.  So deal with it and enjoy it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Charm is a wonderful addition!   <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~hunterx/damlyn.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
