<br>
This I agree with, they need to leave charm alone and fix the zones not the spell. <br>
<br>
Pre-pop all my charm hunting grounds were deep in dungeons where it would often take me 45 minutes of fighting low experience mobs to actually get to the decent experience (and loot) mobs camp, once there I rarely hasted my chosen pet simply because a wipe meant a lengthy cr followed by another 45 minute treck back to the camp spot.<br>
<br>
In pop the gy feature and closeness of the mobs to the zone mean I have to do virtually no work before I can get to the meat of my experiencing and if it goes pear shaped I can be up and running again within 10 minutes, ie. there is little risk.<br>
<br>
How about making us work for our exp like we used to have to, maybe disable the gy feature in certain zones and put the real exp giving mobs behind lesser exp mobs that can't be bypassed and have to be fought. You can be sure if I am faced with a 2 hour cr instead of a 10 minute one I will only be hasting my pet in dire emergencies. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andurravenblade>Andur Ravenblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#333333>(1/15/03 3:42:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=447.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Charm 'nerf' and it's faults.</span><hr size=1> &quot;This I agree with, they need to leave charm alone and fix the zones not the spell. &quot;<br>
